HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 527
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Courtney Nichols on
his selection as the 2024–2025 Cannon County
School District Principal of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding professionals who have devoted their careers to providing
the highest quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Courtney Nichols is one such estimable administrator, who has
distinguished himself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Nichols has been selected as the 2024–2025 Cannon County School
District Principal of the Year, an honor most befitting his outstanding tenure as a principal, as it
recognizes the positive influence he has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, with a career in education spanning thirty-one years, Mr. Nichols is an
extremely talented and compassionate administrator, who works assiduously to motivate his
students, teachers, and staff to reach their full potential as scholars, professionals, and citizens;
and
WHEREAS, Courtney Nichols was initially an agriculture teacher at Richland High
School and transferred to Cannon County High School in 2004 to teach Career and Technical
Education; and
WHEREAS, under his leadership as an FFA advisor, Cannon County High School's
chapter earned numerous State and national honors, and Mr. Nichols was duly named the
NWAE Southeast Agriculture Teacher of the Year; and
